children.subject: from what I know, 170 and 186 are not really much easier, but you will probably still be able to handle them. I would suggest either 188 or data 100, the latter of which is more manageable.

history.content: Personally would advise maybe 188 in this case since 189 and 127 can have a rough workload sometimes and 188 is relevant to the field of AI/ML for seeing a lot of different kinds of AI that exist. 170 is probably a bit much since that is three classes with weekly Problem sets that can be difficult (really depends on you). If you really have no classes, then really pick any of them, since 170 is pretty important for CS majors and 186 and data 100 are pretty solid classes (can't say much about the workloads there).

Hello, I'm cycling between several different schedule choices here and I'd love any feedback! I'm planning to take CS 189 and EE 127 and I want to pick a third, hopefully easier tech to round it out. Next semester I also will have about 8-10 hrs per week of clubs & research.

I'm interested in AI/ML and hoping to go into industry in that space, perhaps after a 5th year masters, but I'm down for SWE jobs as well. I say all this to hopefully provide more context on which classes will be most useful.

So my choices and thoughts for that third tech right now are:

- CS 170

- CS 186

- CS 188

- Data 100

Also if taking three techs (just techs, no other classes) is not a good idea then also just let me know! Thanks so much.
